How to set RO filesystem:
https://hallard.me/raspberry-pi-read-only/

# Arch /boot/cmdline.txt
root=/dev/mmcblk0p2 ro fastboot rootwait noswap console=ttyAMA0,115200 console=tty3 quiet splash loglevel=0 logo.nologo vt.global_cursor_default=0 selinux=0 plymouth.enable=0 smsc95xx.turbo_mode=N dwc_otg.lpm_enable=0 kgdboc=ttyAMA0,115200 elevator=noop

# Arch /etc/fstab
/dev/mmcblk0p1  /boot   	vfat    defaults,ro,errors=remount-ro	0       0
/dev/mmcblk0p3  /var/log   	ext4    defaults        0       0
/dev/mmcblk0p4  /data   	ext4    defaults        0       0
tmpfs   		/var/tmp    tmpfs   nodev,nosuid    0   	0



To enable ro & rw commands
ADD this in /etc/bash.bashrc :

source /root/RPi-tools/rorw/rorw.bashrc
